{"word":"περιστεφής","slug":"περιστεφής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>περιστεφής</b></el> <el>(περι-στεφής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:στέφω'><el>στέφω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>wreathed, crowned</i>, <el>ἀνθέων π.</el> <i>with a crown</i> of flowers, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>twining, encircling</i>, <el>κισσός</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}